    "body": "I am not sure if the link to stdChains is correct here. \r\n\r\nRecently I wanted to interact with bsc testnet. In my repo I had it named \"bsctest\" but then I got an error from foundry saying this name is invalid, maybe I am referring to \"bsc-testnet\".\r\nSo there seems to be a list of how networks should be called according for foundry.\r\nAnd we (in my company) would love to name all networks according to foundry in order to avoid any potential errors.\r\nTherefore I was looking for that list but I cannot find it anywhere in the code.\r\n\r\nThen asked in the Telegram group and @miohtama was so nice to open up this issue here.\r\n\r\nSo my personal goal would just be to find out where to find this list (>> the docs would be a great place for it).\r\nAnd for the foundry project I guess it would be great if there is a standardized/automatic way for adding new networks and updating them in the docs, if that makes sense.",
